In [13]:
data_group1=pd.DataFrame(data=data_group,columns=['Debut'])
data_group1['Debut year'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(data_group['Debut']).year
def generation(row):    
    if (row['Debut year'] > 1991) & (row['Debut year'] < 2004):
        return '1st Generation'
    if (row['Debut year'] > 2003) & (row['Debut year'] < 2013):
        return '2nd Generation'
    if (row['Debut year'] > 2012) & (row['Debut year'] < 2020):
        return '3rd Generation'  
    if (row['Debut year'] > 2019) & (row['Debut year'] < 2023):
        return '4th Generation'
According to https://nolae.eu/blogs/overview/k-pop-generationen-1 , Kpop generations are in the range of years: 1st Generation: 1992 - 2003 2nd Generation: 2003 - 2012 3rd Generation: 2012 - 2019 4th Generation: 2019 - Now

art = df['artists']
foll = df['followers']
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize =(16, 9))

ax.barh(art[0:10], foll[0:10])
for s in ['top', 'bottom', 'left', 'right']:
    ax.spines[s].set_visible(False)
ax.xaxis.set_ticks_position('none')
ax.yaxis.set_ticks_position('none')
ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(pad = 5)
ax.yaxis.set_tick_params(pad = 10)
ax.grid(b = True, color ='grey',
        linestyle ='-.', linewidth = 0.5,
        alpha = 0.2)
 
ax.invert_yaxis()
 
for i in ax.patches:
    plt.text(i.get_width()+0.2, i.get_y()+0.5,
             str(round((i.get_width()), 2)),
             fontsize = 10, fontweight ='bold',
             color ='grey')
ax.set_title('Followers of Idols',
             loc ='left', )
plt.show()
